---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Robotics for Good Youth Challenge - Belgium 2026">

    <!-- Hero Section with Black Background and Geometric Gradients -->
    <section class="relative min-h-screen overflow-hidden bg-black">
        <!-- Geometric gradient shapes inspired by the reference image -->
        <div class="absolute inset-0">
            <!-- Orange triangle from bottom-left -->
            <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-1/2 h-3/4 bg-gradient-to-tr from-orange-500 via-orange-400 to-transparent opacity-80" style="clip-path: polygon(0 100%, 50% 50%, 0 0);"></div>

            <!-- Yellow/Gold triangle from top -->
            <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/4 w-1/3 h-1/2 bg-gradient-to-b from-yellow-400 via-yellow-300 to-transparent opacity-70" style="clip-path: polygon(50% 0, 100% 100%, 0 100%);"></div>

            <!-- Green triangle from right -->
            <div class="absolute right-0 top-1/4 w-1/2 h-2/3 bg-gradient-to-l from-green-400 via-green-300 to-transparent opacity-70" style="clip-path: polygon(100% 0, 100% 100%, 50% 50%);"></div>

            <!-- Blue triangle from bottom-right -->
            <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 w-1/2 h-2/3 bg-gradient-to-tl from-blue-500 via-cyan-400 to-transparent opacity-75" style="clip-path: polygon(100% 100%, 100% 0, 50% 100%);"></div>

            <!-- Pink/Purple accent -->
            <div class="absolute top-1/3 left-1/3 w-1/3 h-1/3 bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-500 via-purple-500 to-transparent opacity-40 blur-3xl"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-5xl relative z-10 py-20">
            <div class="text-center mb-16">

                <div class="mb-12">
                    <a href="/" class="text-white/60 hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm uppercase tracking-wide font-bold">
                        ← Back to Home
                    </a>
                </div>

                <!-- Hero Image with frame effect -->
                <div class="mb-12 relative">
                    <div class="relative inline-block">
                        <img
                            src="/robotics-for-good/Robotics-for-Good-Youth-Challenge.png"
                            alt="Robotics for Good Youth Challenge"
                            class="w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto rounded-3xl shadow-2xl border-4 border-white/10"
                        />
                        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/30 to-transparent rounded-3xl"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Logo -->
                <div class="mb-10">
                    <img
                        src="/nskids-full-logo-transparent.png"
                        alt="North Star Kids"
                        class="h-24 md:h-32 object-contain mx-auto"
                        style="filter: drop-shadow(0 8px 24px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3));"
                    />
                </div>

                <!-- Date Badge -->
                <div class="mb-8">
                    <span class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-white text-black font-bold text-lg md:text-xl uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full shadow-2xl">
                        National Finals: March 21, 2026
                    </span>
                </div>

                <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold text-white mb-8 leading-tight" style="text-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);">
                    Robotics for Good<br>Youth Challenge
                </h1>

                <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-white/90 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed font-semibold" style="text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);">
                    Belgium 2025-26 Season
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Blog Content Section -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-b from-black via-gray-900 to-black">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl">
            <article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">

                <h2>Official National Organizer for Belgium</h2>

                <p>North Star Kids has been appointed by the ITU (International Telecommunication Union) as the official National Organizer for Belgium for the 2025–26 season.</p>

                <p>As national organizers, we:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Recruit and train schools and teams across Belgium.</li>
                    <li>Host the Belgian National Robotics for Good Youth Challenge, with the national championship taking place on Saturday, 21 March 2026.</li>
                    <li>Mentor the winning Junior and Senior teams as they prepare to represent Belgium at the Global Finals in Geneva, Switzerland.</li>
                    <li>Build partnerships that make robotics and innovation accessible to more young people across the country.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Season 2025–26: Robotics for Agriculture</h2>

                <p>The upcoming season focuses on "Robotics for Food Security." With global food systems under pressure, learners will explore how robotics can help:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Improve irrigation and reduce water waste</li>
                    <li>Support precision farming with selective planting</li>
                    <li>Harvest and sort crops efficiently while protecting ecosystems</li>
                </ul>

                <p>This challenge gives young innovators the chance to design robots that directly address food security, sustainability, and climate resilience.</p>

                <h2>Belgium Finals</h2>

                <p>The national championship for Belgium will take place on <strong>Saturday, 21st March 2026</strong>.</p>

                <p>The winners from each category will represent Belgium at the Grand Finale in Geneva, Switzerland, during the AI for Good Global Summit from 7–10 July 2026.</p>

                <h3>Winners Benefits</h3>

                <p>Benefits awarded to the winning teams in both junior and senior categories:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Robotics for Good Youth Challenge Grand Finale ticket</li>
                    <li>Team Pod at the AI for Good Global Summit</li>
                    <li>Exclusive Passes for the AI for Good Global Summit
                        <ul>
                            <li>General passes for each team member</li>
                            <li>"Leaders Pass" (1) for sponsor</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Invitation to mentorship session with industry experts before Grand Finale</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Featured Media Content</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li>Interview article on winning teams (AI for Good channels)</li>
                    <li>Featured prominently in North Star Kids article on the Belgian ITU Finale</li>
                    <li>Visibility on AI for Good channels & platforms</li>
                    <li>Neural Network Innovation Factory Exhibition</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Call for Participation</h2>

                <p class="text-xl font-semibold">2025-26 Season is now OPEN!</p>

                <h3>Schools & Teams</h3>

                <p>Compete for a chance to represent Belgium at the global stage in Geneva. Registration is now open for the 2025–26 season!</p>

                <p><strong>Participation Categories</strong></p>

                <p>Individuals as well as teams consisting of up to 8 members can register:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Junior</strong> – Born between 2016 – 2012</li>
                    <li><strong>Senior</strong> – Born between 2011 – 2008</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Why Participate</strong></p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Showcase innovation at the National championship</li>
                    <li>Chance to represent Belgium at the AI for Good Global Summit in Geneva</li>
                    <li>Hands-on exposure to robotics, AI and teamwork</li>
                    <li>Mentorship by robotics and AI experts</li>
                    <li>Certificates and recognition for all participants</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="not-prose my-8">
                    <a
                        href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd4j4whmwHq7ID37gZQpbzF99EUXJ3FKxxC0INE6YOWVEwZyw/viewform?usp=dialog"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        class="inline-block px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold bg-white text-black rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors"
                    >
                        Register as a Team →
                    </a>
                </div>

                <h3>Organisations & Partners</h3>

                <p>Help us bring the Robotics for Good Challenge closer to students across Belgium! Partner with us to host or organize regional cluster events in your region.</p>

                <p><strong>Why Collaborate</strong></p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Host regional qualifiers in your region</li>
                    <li>Recognition as a regional host partner on all event materials</li>
                    <li>Showcase your institution as a STEM hub</li>
                    <li>Visibility within the region as a champion of youth innovation</li>
                    <li>Direct engagement with schools and learners in their area</li>
                    <li>Opportunity to nurture and connect with young innovators locally</li>
                    <li>Recognition on North Star Kids platforms as an official partner</li>
                </ul>

                <p>If you are interested in a partnership, reach out to the North Star Kids Lead: <a href="mailto:vasiliki@ns2agi.com">vasiliki@ns2agi.com</a></p>

                <h3>Sponsors</h3>

                <p>Empower the next generation of innovators while gaining global visibility. Join us as a sponsor of the Robotics for Good Youth Challenge – Belgium 2026.</p>

                <p><strong>Benefits to Sponsors</strong></p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Featured visibility at the AI for Good Global Summit in Geneva via the ITU <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1rFjNiAIGrMAmnIvnxRF49SgkgdVDmVG7/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank">sponsorship package</a></li>
                    <li>Logo placement and acknowledgement at national finals and regional events</li>
                    <li>Positive CSR impact and alignment with STEM, digital skills, and youth empowerment</li>
                    <li>Empower Belgian youth to compete on a global innovation stage</li>
                    <li>Be recognized as a champion of STEM education and digital skills</li>
                    <li>Media exposure through our national and partner networks</li>
                </ul>

                <p>If you are interested in becoming a sponsor, reach out to our partnerships lead: <a href="mailto:cedric@ns2agi.com">cedric@ns2agi.com</a></p>

                <hr class="my-12 border-white/20">

                <h3>Questions?</h3>

                <p>Reach out to us anytime!</p>

                <div class="not-prose flex gap-6 my-6">
                    <a href="https://www.instagram.com/northstaragi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-white/60 hover:text-white transition-colors">
                        <svg class="w-8 h-8" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
